### Design System Notes

All components follow consistent patterns:
- **Geomanist font family** for typography
- **CSS custom properties** for theming and colors
- **Responsive-first design** with standard Tailwind breakpoints (sm, md, lg)
- **Semantic HTML** with proper accessibility features
- **Alpine.js integration** for interactive components
- **TypeScript interfaces** for prop validation
- **Slot-based composition** for flexible content placement


### Colors system

The project uses a comprehensive CSS custom properties color system defined in `/src/styles/colors.css`. All components automatically adapt to theme changes via CSS variables.

Use colors with inline style like: style="background-color: var(--bg-100)"

Never use colors like bg-[#000] always use variables

#### Base Color Palette

**Utility Colors:**
- `--u-white` (#FFFFFF) - Pure white with opacity variants (5%, 10%, 20%, 50%, 70%)
- `--u-black` (#01080F) - Deep black with opacity variants (5%, 10%, 20%, 50%, 70%)
- `--u-light-blue` (#D9ECFD) - Light blue accent color
- `--u-blue` (#1D9BF0) - Primary blue
- `--u-dark-blue` (#252476) - Dark blue for gradients and accents

**Gray Scale:**
- `--u-gray-100` (#F9F9F9) - Lightest gray
- `--u-gray-200` (#F1F1F1) - Light gray
- `--u-gray-300` (#E2E2E2) - Medium gray
- `--u-gray-400` (#DEDEDE) - Medium-dark gray
- `--u-gray-500` (#A9A9A9) - Dark gray

#### Semantic Color Variables

Components use semantic variables that change based on theme:
- `--bg` - Main background color
- `--text` - Primary text color
- `--text-light` - Secondary/muted text
- `--primary` - Primary brand color
- `--accent-color` - Accent/highlight color
- `--link-bg` - Button/link background
- `--separator` - Border/divider lines
- `--card-border` - Card and component borders

#### Theme Modes

**Light Mode (default):**
- Clean white backgrounds with dark text
- Light gray accents and borders

**Dark Mode (`data-theme="dark"`):**
- Dark backgrounds with white text
- Semi-transparent overlays for depth

**Light Gray Mode (`data-theme="light-gray"`):**
- Light gray background with white cards
- Subtle contrast for content sections

**Light Blue Mode (`data-theme="light-blue"`):**
- Light blue background with white elements
- Soft, approachable aesthetic

#### Best Practices

- Always use semantic variable names in components (e.g., `--text`, `--bg`)
- Add opacity variants for utility colors when needed
- Test new colors across all theme modes
- Maintain accessibility contrast ratios
- Use existing semantic variables when possible before creating new ones
